 Exercise 6 is based on a drawing, which represents a certain rectangular terrain. 

00:04:00.780 --> 00:04:05.600
 The exercise asks that, from the drawing, find the correct statement 

00:04:05.680 --> 00:04:08.840
 involving the concepts of area and perimeter. 

00:04:08.960 --> 00:04:14.580
 Looking at the drawing, we see that one side is represented by (x + 6) 

00:04:14.635 --> 00:04:16.635
 and another by (3x). 

00:04:16.640 --> 00:04:24.720
 In this way, to find the area would be necessary to multiply the terms: (x + 6). 3x 

00:04:24.760 --> 00:04:28.600
 Already the perimeter would be found by the sum of the sides 

00:04:28.680 --> 00:04:36.640
 (3x + 3x + x + 6 + x + 6) = 132. 

00:04:36.720 --> 00:04:38.780
 then the correct statement 

00:04:38.780 --> 00:04:40.116
 is the alternative D 

00:04:40.180 --> 00:04:43.100
 which says that the perimeter is equal to 132. 

